    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have tested this on Arch Linux and FreeBSD without plugins or anything using the `--clean` option.\n\nYou open a Markdown file that is about 100K. Search for a specific word that occurs more than once in the text, the more the word occurs, the slower the problem gets. Then, while the word is highlighted around in the text, just place the cursor at the beginning of a specific sentence at about the middle of the document and move the cursor from left to right. The cursor will display clear sluggish behavior, lag, etc.\n\nI did a syntime to test and compare the same file on Vim.\n\nResult on Neovim NVIM v0.10.4:\n\n```\nTOTAL      COUNT  MATCH   SLOWEST     AVERAGE   NAME               PATTERN\n0.550669   5369   0       0.000488    0.000103  markdownOrderedListMarker \\%(\\t\\| \\{0,4}\\)\\<\\d\\+\\.\\%(\\s\\+\\S\\)\\@=\n0.480087   5369   290     0.000450    0.000089  markdownListMarker \\%(\\t\\| \\{0,4\\}\\)[-*+]\\%(\\s\\+\\S\\)\\@=\n0.291542   5369   0       0.000262    0.000054  markdownH6          \\{,3}######\\s\n0.288218   5369   0       0.000262    0.000054  markdownH5          \\{,3}#####\\s\n0.288125   5369   0       0.000261    0.000054  markdownH4          \\{,3}####\\s\n0.288080   5369   0       0.000261    0.000054  markdownH3          \\{,3}###\\s\n0.286361   5369   0       0.000260    0.000053  markdownH2          \\{,3}##\\s\n0.285438   5369   0       0.000264    0.000053  markdownH1          \\{,3}#\\s\n0.179679   3770   3770    0.000157    0.000048  markdownBold       \\S\\@<=\\*\\*\\|^$\n...\n```\n\nResult on Vim 9.1:\n\n```\nTOTAL      COUNT  MATCH   SLOWEST     AVERAGE   NAME               PATTERN\n0.002851   12     0       0.000367    0.000238  markdownListMarker \\%(\\t\\| \\{0,4\\}\\)[-*+]\\%(\\s\\+\\S\\)\\@=\n0.002771   12     0       0.000350    0.000231  markdownOrderedListMarker \\%(\\t\\| \\{0,4}\\)\\<\\d\\+\\.\\%(\\s\\+\\S\\)\\@=\n0.001518   12     0       0.000203    0.000127  markdownH1          \\{,3}#\\s\n0.001516   12     0       0.000197    0.000126  markdownH5          \\{,3}#####\\s\n0.001514   12     0       0.000198    0.000126  markdownH2          \\{,3}##\\s\n0.001499   12     0       0.000195    0.000125  markdownH4          \\{,3}####\\s\n0.001494   12     0       0.000199    0.000125  markdownH3          \\{,3}###\\s\n0.001494   12     0       0.000197    0.000125  markdownH6          \\{,3}######\\s\n0.000810   12     0       0.000109    0.000068  markdownLinkText   !\\=\\[\\%(\\_[^][]*\\%(\\[\\_[^][]*\\]\\_[^][]*\\)*]\\%( \\=[[(]\\)\\)\\@=\n0.000777   8      8       0.000106    0.000097  markdownBold       \\S\\@<=\\*\\*\\|^$\n...\n```\n\nI have noticed this behavior for months, but have just now had time to file a report.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean foo.md\nSearch for specific word that occurs about 10 times in the document.\nGo to something like line 100, place cursor at the start and move it to the right.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSmoth scrolling, as in Vim, not sluggish.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux and FreeBSD 14.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nXTerm(397) and XTerm(397)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nPacman",
